        "id": 4288,
        "title": "Youth leading agriculture extension: Meet Angelique, a YEAN PEALE Extension Officer in Musanze District, Northern Rwanda",
        "slug": null,
        "image": "/uploads/media-1705175778539-129426030.jpeg",
        "text": "<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">Uzamukunda Angelique lives in Musanse, she has a bachelor’s degree in crop science from the university of Rwanda, College of agriculture and veterinary medicine (UR-CAVM). She manifested interests to join YEAN Private Extension and Advisory Learning Experience (PEALE) together with other 136 candidates shortlisted from the whole cohort of  650 fresh graduates (382 M, 268f)  from UR-CAVM cohort of the year 2022. At the time of her enrollment for the YEAN PEALE program in February 2023, Angelique was not connected to the community and extension programs like other new job seekers and she did not have a twitter account, a LinkedIn page or a professional membership in any agri value chain platforms. When asked about the reason she is joining the program, Angelique mentioned that she wants to learn more about modern agriculture, recent advances in the agriculture sector and get an experience of working with farmers for her to advance her career and perhaps find ways to start her own agribusiness. She completed the core engagement stage of the program and got the opportunity to be considered in the first cohort of YEAN  extension officers deployed in Musanze (her home), Nyabihu, Rubavu, Kicukiro, Gasabo, Rwamagana and Kayonza districts to be part of AIRTEA 3</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 0.6em;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">rd</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"> party project ‘</span><span style=\"color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">Youth Leading changes in Resilient Private Extension and Advisory Services for Job and Wealth Creation</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">’ implemented by a consortium of YEAN, RAB and UNILAK. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align:none;\"><img src=\"https://lh7-us.googleusercontent.com/naTyxwJel-lTD3UdVmN-XoGxgVsgnHIl2orhNfvm3TR6r9DwHWgHCb5nN_zgGVrFMVjPQeq_9iy10YIoENRNjLLPnklV-tcrgsazGDBT4R-BTFi35vJEmyJkHwkH_jw76H5HiXehYnYd\" alt=\"\" style=\"height: ;width: \"/></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">Angelique wished to increase her knowledge and experience while impacting her community and playing a significant role in the objectives of YEAN of young people leading agriculture transformation in their communities. In her first action plan as YEAN PEALE Extension Officer deployed in Musanze, Angelique planned to train individual farmers and cooperatives on modern agriculture, soil conservation and other good agricultural practices. Angelique is pursuing her goal with the YEAN and AIRTEA project with commitment and dedication to impact her community. Angelique is providing extension services to her community’s farmers cooperatives. She works with the KOTEMUSHI cooperative in the Musanze District, Shingiro sector, with 143 members (41F, 102M) on 15Ha, a cooperative</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"> of </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">smallholder farmers</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"> that produces Irish potato and other crops like Onion</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">. She is coaching farmers on applying good agricultural practices ensuring that farmers adhered to the recommended inputs standards.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><strong>About YEAN PEALE</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);background-color: transparent;font-size: 12pt;font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">YEAN Private Extension and Advisory Learning Experience is a youth led learning program co-designed for aspiring youth to become private extensionists. The program increases the level of skills for aspiring extension agents in response to the growing demand from the farming communities. Youth selected to attend YEAN PEALE complete 3 stages. The CORE ENGAGEMENT STAGE: which is the first and mandatory One month online learning phase followed by the  BLENDED LEARNING STAGE where in  5 to 7 months selected candidates commit for 5 to 10 days a month for community and practical engagement in the agricultural value chain. The last stage is the PEER TO PEER LEARNING STAGE. Participants who have completed at least 3 of 6 modules of New Extensionist Learning Kit (NEKL) and 18 days of community work join the peer to peer learning stage. Under this final learning stage, some learners decide to continue their career as program peer to peer coaches (extension professionals) while others gain more exposure to secure economic opportunities (further studies, employment). As of December 2023, the YEAN PEALE program had 135 learners (87 male, 48 female) with 18 successfully linked to agriculture opportunities. </span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n",
