        "id": 4289,
        "title": "Empowering Agriculture and harnessing agripreneurship: The Effectiveness of Youth-Led Extension Services",
        "slug": null,
        "image": "/uploads/media-1713540091039-136306539.jpeg",
        "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">Tackling the potential of youth-led extension services turns out to be a game changer in the field of agriculture, where creativity and resilience to shocks caused by climate change are critical. These services, led by young people, give agricultural activities a new outlook and a dynamic approach, which increases their overall effectiveness.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">The ability of youth-led agriculture extension services to establish connections with rural communities other young farmers is one of its main advantages and it’s one of the reasons YEAN has opted for this approach which leads to increased engagement of young people in agriculture. These young leaders -as we call them- effectively disseminate important information on improved and climate smart practices, market trends, sustainable practices, and advanced agriculture techniques since they have relatable communication styles couple with knowledge. This relevance encourages participation and trust, which increases the adoption of recommended agricultural practices among farmers.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">Furthermore, there's no doubt that youth-led extension programs are frequently marked by a strong sense of passion and excitement. This enthusiasm is demonstrated by aggressive outreach programs, creative problem-solving techniques, and a readiness to try out innovative ideas. Such energy injects a renewed sense of vigour into agricultural communities, inspiring innovation, and resilience in the face of challenges like climate change and market fluctuations.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">In addition, by enabling young people to serve as agricultural extension agents, the urgent problem of youth unemployment is addressed while simultaneously developing the next generation of agricultural leaders. Through offering them chances for skill enhancement, leadership directions, and guidance, YEAN cultivates a group of capable individuals who can spearhead the advancement of sustainable agriculture, innovations in agribusiness and ensure food security.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Montserrat;\">YEAN has chosen this single path of youth-led agriculture extension services which represent a potent force for positive change in agricultural communities. YEAN is working with our partners organizations and farmer’s associations and has deployed around 80 youth who are proactively working with farmers providing proximity extension and advisory services. We believe in their capacity to inspire, create, and connect what makes them so powerful; in the end, they clear the path for a more robust and prosperous agricultural future. YEAN aims to reach 150,000 farmers by year 2025 through youth led private extension and advisory services provision which is a contribution to our long term vision of transforming traditional subsistence agriculture into agribusiness through youth innovations as skilled and powerful weapon for leading the change toward sustainable livelihood.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n",
